{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:03.461 --> 00:04.879
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:04.963 --> 00:07.632
{\an7}♪ ADVENTURE IS CALLING,
SHE CAN'T STAY AWAY ♪

00:07.716 --> 00:11.094
{\an7}♪ HER ARMOR IS SPARKLING,
HER COURAGE IS GREAT ♪

00:11.177 --> 00:14.389
{\an7}♪ HER NECKLACE IS GLOWING,
NOW SHE'LL FIND A WAY ♪

00:14.472 --> 00:16.766
{\an7}♪ WITH HELP FROM
HER BEST FRIENDS ♪

00:16.850 --> 00:18.768
{\an8}♪ THEY'LL SAVE THE DAY ♪

00:18.852 --> 00:20.103
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:20.186 --> 00:22.188
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:22.272 --> 00:25.900
{\an7}♪ TRUE TO HERSELF,
DOING WHAT'S RIGHT ♪

00:25.984 --> 00:27.235
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:27.318 --> 00:30.029
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:34.784 --> 00:38.079
THIS IS IT, TRINKET.
ARE YOU READY?

00:38.163 --> 00:41.541
UNICORNS ARE BORN
READY AND SPARKLY.

00:41.624 --> 00:44.794
WE FINALLY GET TO
SHARE OUR FLOWERY...

00:44.878 --> 00:46.129
SPARKLY...

00:46.212 --> 00:47.797
PRINCESSY...

00:47.881 --> 00:49.924
TIARAS!

00:47.881 --> 00:49.924
TIARAS! OOH!

00:50.008 --> 00:51.217
COACH:
HUP HUP HUP.

00:51.301 --> 00:52.886
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

00:52.969 --> 00:54.512
OK. LISTEN UP,
EVERYONE.

00:54.596 --> 00:56.973
TODAY IS LEARNALOT
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL'S

00:57.056 --> 00:58.975
ANNUAL SHARE FAIRE.

00:59.058 --> 01:00.393
YOU MAKE IT.

01:00.477 --> 01:04.980
THEN YOU SHARE IT,
SO LET'S GET SHARING.

01:05.063 --> 01:07.817
{\an1}WOW, LOOK AT ALL
THESE STANDS, TRINK.

01:07.901 --> 01:10.111
{\an1}EVERYONE'S GOT SOMETHING
TO SHARE TODAY.

01:10.195 --> 01:11.404
BALLOON SWORDS.

01:11.488 --> 01:13.907
{\an1}GET YOUR HAND-TWISTED
BALLOON SWORDS HERE

01:13.990 --> 01:15.950
AT SIR BLAINE'S STAND.

01:16.034 --> 01:18.411
MOO! FRUIT.

01:18.495 --> 01:21.831
FRESH, TASTY
FRUIT.

01:21.915 --> 01:24.250
RAAR! RAAR!

01:24.334 --> 01:27.504
SOCK PUPPETS,
HOMEMADE SOCK PUPPETS.

01:27.587 --> 01:30.173
{\an1}AW, GARRETT,
THAT'S SO COOL.

01:30.256 --> 01:31.925
PRETTY COOL,
HUH, NELLA?

01:32.008 --> 01:33.176
I'M MAKING
ONE OF EACH

01:33.259 --> 01:34.511
OF MY FAVORITE
CREATURES.

01:34.594 --> 01:37.138
AND I'M MAKING ONE
OF ALL MY BESTEST BUDDIES.

01:37.222 --> 01:40.183
TRINKET, SAY HELLO
TO PUPPET TRINKET.

01:40.266 --> 01:43.228
{\an1}IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO BE ME?

01:43.311 --> 01:44.521
YEP.
"HI, TRINKET."

01:44.604 --> 01:49.359
{\an1}HARD TO BELIEVE IT'S JUST
ONE OF MY REALLY OLD SOCKS.

01:50.443 --> 01:53.446
UH, WE BETTER GET BACK
TO OUR STAND.

01:53.530 --> 01:55.865
{\an7}YEP. OUR FLOWERY,
SPARKLY, PRINCESSY TIARAS

01:55.949 --> 01:58.743
{\an7}AREN'T GONNA
SHARE THEMSELVES.

01:58.827 --> 01:59.744
MINATORI: NOOOO!

01:59.828 --> 02:02.664
{\an8}WILLOW: OH, NO.
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

02:02.747 --> 02:04.999
{\an1}WILLOW, MINATORI,
WHAT'S WRONG?

02:05.083 --> 02:06.292
OUR TREE.

02:06.376 --> 02:08.377
{\an1}IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
AN APPLE TREE,

02:08.461 --> 02:10.547
BUT IT'S GROWING
LEMONS.

02:10.630 --> 02:12.632
{\an1}WE MUST HAVE PLANTED
THE WRONG SEEDS.

02:12.715 --> 02:15.218
UGH! AND THESE LEMONS
ARE TOO SOUR TO EAT.

02:15.301 --> 02:16.845
WE CAN'T
SHARE THESE.

02:16.928 --> 02:20.056
MAYBE NOT, BUT YOU CAN
ALWAYS MAKE LEMONADE.

02:20.139 --> 02:21.808
{\an8}LEMONADE?

02:20.139 --> 02:21.808
{\an8}LEMONADE?

02:21.891 --> 02:23.393
{\an8}SURE.

02:23.476 --> 02:26.271
{\an1}♪ WHEN YOU GET LEMONS,
MAKE A NEW PLAN ♪

02:26.354 --> 02:28.398
♪ YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE AFRAID ♪

02:28.481 --> 02:29.941
♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

02:30.024 --> 02:32.110
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

02:32.193 --> 02:35.697
{\an1}♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
TURN THEM AROUND ♪

02:35.780 --> 02:38.533
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

02:38.616 --> 02:41.161
MM! THIS LEMONADE
IS YUMMY.

02:41.244 --> 02:44.247
{\an7}WHAT A GREAT IDEA.
THANK YOU, PRINCESS NELLA.

02:44.330 --> 02:48.459
{\an1}TRINKET: NELLA, WE NEED
YOUR DAZZLING CRAFTS SKILLS.

02:48.543 --> 02:51.296
{\an1}EVERYONE WANTS SOME
OF OUR FLOWERY, SPARKLY,

02:51.379 --> 02:52.964
PRINCESSY TIARAS.

02:53.047 --> 02:54.424
OH, SO SPECIAL.

02:54.507 --> 02:56.217
AH, A TRUE
WORK OF ART.

02:56.301 --> 03:00.388
WOW. GOOD THING WE'VE GOT
A WHOLE TRAY OF FLOWERS.

03:00.471 --> 03:04.058
FLOWERS? WHAT'S SO
SPECIAL ABOUT FLOWERS?

03:04.142 --> 03:05.476
COACH: HUP HUP HUP HUP.

03:05.560 --> 03:08.062
SIR COACH,
BALLOON SWORD?

03:08.146 --> 03:09.230
NOT FOR ME, BLAINE.

03:09.314 --> 03:11.900
{\an1}I'VE GOT TO GET
ONE OF THOSE TIARAS.

03:11.983 --> 03:13.443
HUP HUP HUP.

03:11.983 --> 03:13.443
OHH...

03:13.526 --> 03:15.445
AMAZING.
WHAT A TIARA.

03:15.528 --> 03:17.280
IT LOOKS
BEAUTIFUL ON YOU.

03:17.363 --> 03:20.033
I WORKED SO HARD
ON MY BALLOONS,

03:20.116 --> 03:21.075
AND NOBODY
WANTS THEM.

03:21.159 --> 03:24.746
AND ALL BECAUSE OF
NELLA'S FLOWERS,

03:24.829 --> 03:28.249
AND THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO ABOUT IT...

03:28.333 --> 03:31.920
OR IS THERE?

03:34.213 --> 03:37.550
THEY'LL ALL BE RUNNING
TO MY STAND

03:37.634 --> 03:41.304
WHEN NELLA'S FLOWERS
ARE GONE.

03:41.387 --> 03:44.390
OOPSIE. SORRY, FLOWERS.

03:44.474 --> 03:46.935
{\an1}NELLA CAN'T MAKE TIARAS
OUT OF YOU NOW.

03:47.018 --> 03:50.313
TRINKET: HOLD ON, NELLA.
I'LL GO GET SOME MORE...

03:50.396 --> 03:53.191
FLOWERS! NELLA,
OUR FLOWERS,

03:53.274 --> 03:55.276
THEY'VE BEEN
SQUASHED.

03:55.360 --> 03:57.236
OH, NO.

03:55.360 --> 03:57.236
OK, OK.

03:57.320 --> 03:59.989
STAY CALM, TRINKET.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.491
WHAT ARE
WE GONNA DO?

04:01.574 --> 04:03.117
WAIT A MINUTE.

04:03.201 --> 04:05.161
{\an1}THESE AREN'T HORRIBLY
SQUASHED FLOWERS.

04:05.244 --> 04:08.957
{\an1}THESE ARE BEAUTIFULLY
PRESSED FLOWERS,

04:09.040 --> 04:12.251
AND THEY'LL MAKE AMAZING,
PRESSED-FLOWER NECKLACES.

04:12.335 --> 04:14.545
THEY WILL?

04:12.335 --> 04:14.545
YEP, BECAUSE...

04:14.629 --> 04:17.173
{\an1}♪ WHEN THINGS LOOK BITTER,
MAKE IT ALL BETTER ♪

04:17.257 --> 04:18.966
{\an1}♪ IT'S ALL
GONNA BE OK ♪

04:19.050 --> 04:21.844
♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

04:21.928 --> 04:23.930
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

04:24.013 --> 04:26.474
♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

04:26.557 --> 04:28.059
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

04:28.142 --> 04:33.439
OK, SO TIARAS
ARE SO 5 MINUTES AGO.

04:33.523 --> 04:38.611
WHO WANTS A FANCY,
PRESSED-FLOWER NECKLACE?

04:38.695 --> 04:40.363
OH, I DO.
I'LL TAKE 5.

04:40.446 --> 04:41.948
OOH, ME, PLEASE.

04:42.031 --> 04:43.032
DRAGON BURPS.

04:43.116 --> 04:45.493
EVERYONE'S STILL
AT NELLA'S STAND,

04:45.576 --> 04:47.120
AND NOT AT MINE.

04:47.203 --> 04:49.205
OH, NELLA
NEVER GIVES UP.

04:49.288 --> 04:54.127
WELL, NEITHER DO I.

04:54.210 --> 04:56.421
{\an1}WELL, YOU DEFINITELY
CAN'T MAKE FLOWERY TIARAS

04:56.504 --> 05:00.633
OR NECKLACES WITHOUT
ANY FLOWERS AT ALL.

05:00.717 --> 05:05.346
{\an1}TODAY'S WEATHER--CLOUDY
WITH A CHANCE OF FLOWERS.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.140
{\an1}HA HA HA!

05:08.182 --> 05:11.019
HEY, LOOK, NELLA.
OUR FLOWERS ARE FLYING.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.186
[GASPS]

05:12.270 --> 05:13.563
OUR FLOWERS ARE FLYING!

05:13.646 --> 05:14.564
FLYING FLOWERS?

05:14.647 --> 05:18.735
{\an1}"I'VE GOT IT.
I'VE GOT IT." OOF!

05:18.818 --> 05:21.070
"I DON'T GOT IT."

05:21.154 --> 05:23.906
AFTER THOSE FLOWERS.

05:26.325 --> 05:29.162
{\an1}THERE THEY ARE.
JUMP, TRINK.

05:30.079 --> 05:32.457
GOTCHA.

05:32.540 --> 05:35.251
{\an1}WHOO HOO!

05:32.540 --> 05:35.251
WAY TO GO, NELLA.

05:35.334 --> 05:36.586
HOW DOES SHE DO THAT?

05:36.669 --> 05:38.421
{\an1}YAY!

05:36.669 --> 05:38.421
OH, WAY TO GO, NELLA.

05:38.504 --> 05:41.549
{\an1}GREAT JOB, NELLA.
YOU CAUGHT OUR FLOWERS--

05:41.632 --> 05:44.677
OH, LOOK--BUT ALL
THE PETALS HAVE FALLEN OFF.

05:44.761 --> 05:47.138
ALL WE HAVE LEFT ARE--

05:47.221 --> 05:49.599
THE TWISTY STEMS.

05:49.682 --> 05:51.684
♪ NO TIARAS,
NO NECKLACES ♪

05:51.768 --> 05:54.645
♪ GO, BLAINE,
GO, BLAINE ♪

05:54.729 --> 05:56.272
NELLA: I'VE GOT IT.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.982
WE CAN TAKE
THESE TWISTY STEMS

05:58.066 --> 06:00.276
AND MAKE THEM
INTO TWISTY, SPARKLY

06:00.359 --> 06:00.818
FRIENDSHIP
BRACELETS.

06:00.902 --> 06:03.404
COME ON, TRINK.

06:03.488 --> 06:04.280
{\an1}♪ WHEN THINGS LOOK BITTER,
MAKE IT ALL BETTER ♪

06:04.363 --> 06:07.158
{\an1}♪ IT'S ALL
GONNA BE OK ♪

06:07.241 --> 06:09.994
{\an1}BOTH: ♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

06:10.078 --> 06:12.163
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

06:12.246 --> 06:14.791
♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

06:14.874 --> 06:17.460
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

06:17.543 --> 06:18.836
IDA: OH, YOU
HAVE BRACELETS.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.714
I LOVE THEM.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.714
BRACELETS?

06:21.798 --> 06:24.467
RRGH! MY BALLOON!

06:24.550 --> 06:29.138
[PBBT]

06:29.847 --> 06:31.641
MINATORI,
BE CAREFUL.

06:31.724 --> 06:33.935
USING TOO MUCH OF MY
SPECIAL PLANT FOOD

06:34.018 --> 06:36.479
CAN CAUSE BIG
PROBLEMS FOR PLANTS.

06:36.562 --> 06:38.147
OOPS. SORRY.

06:38.231 --> 06:41.234
{\an1}DON'T WANT TO CAUSE
ANY BIG PROBLEMS.

06:41.317 --> 06:43.152
BIG PROBLEMS?

06:43.236 --> 06:47.406
{\an1}WELL, BIG PROBLEMS ARE
EXACTLY WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR.

06:49.617 --> 06:51.661
{\an1}I'LL JUST USE
THIS SUPER PLANT FOOD

06:51.744 --> 06:53.663
TO MESS UP NELLA'S PLAN.

06:53.746 --> 06:58.251
{\an1}OOH, THAT'LL
STOP HER FOR SURE.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.712
JUST GETTING SOME MORE
FLOWER STEMS, TRINK.

07:01.796 --> 07:04.006
BE RIGHT BACK.

07:04.090 --> 07:05.716
[GASPS]

07:05.800 --> 07:10.054
WHAT'S HAPPENING
TO OUR FLOWERS?

07:10.138 --> 07:13.099
WHOA!

07:13.182 --> 07:14.308
TRINKET: NELLA, I HAVE
THE BEST IDEA FOR THE BRACELETS.

07:14.392 --> 07:17.311
WHOA. WHERE DID
THAT COME FROM?

07:17.395 --> 07:20.648
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW.
IT JUST SHOT UP.

07:20.731 --> 07:26.362
UH, NELLA, I DON'T LIKE
THE LOOK OF THIS.

07:26.445 --> 07:27.697
WHOA! WHAT
IS THAT?

07:27.780 --> 07:29.490
{\an1}EVERYBODY,
LOOK OUT.

07:29.574 --> 07:31.117
COACH: UH-OH.

07:29.574 --> 07:31.117
{\an1}MAN: RUN!

07:31.200 --> 07:33.369
{\an1}IDA: OH, UTA, RUN.
WHOA! LOOK OUT!

07:33.452 --> 07:36.205
{\an8}OUR STAND!

07:33.452 --> 07:36.205
{\an8}OUR BRACELETS!

07:36.289 --> 07:38.875
{\an1}NOW LET'S SEE WHO WANTS
NELLA'S FLOWERS.

07:38.958 --> 07:41.878
OH, WAIT. NO ONE.
HOO HOO HOO!

07:41.961 --> 07:45.423
{\an1}IT'S MY TURN TO SHINE.
BALLOON SWORDS.

07:45.506 --> 07:47.508
COME AND GET
YOUR BALLOON SWORDS

07:47.592 --> 07:50.428
{\an1}TO PROTECT YOU
FROM GIANT PLANTS.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.554
{\an1}MAN:
RUN AWAY!

07:51.637 --> 07:52.680
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

07:52.763 --> 07:54.473
TAKE COVER.

07:54.557 --> 07:55.933
{\an7}LOOK OUT!

07:56.017 --> 07:58.603
GOLLY GOBLETS, THAT'S
ONE BIG FLOWER, NELLA.

07:58.686 --> 08:00.938
AND IT'S RUINING
EVERYTHING.

08:01.022 --> 08:03.566
{\an1}I KNOW, EVEN IF IT IS
KIND OF PRETTY.

08:03.649 --> 08:05.610
MINATORI: OH, NO!

08:05.693 --> 08:06.611
OUR LEMONADE!

08:05.693 --> 08:06.611
OUR LEMONADE!

08:06.694 --> 08:11.032
{\an1}WAIT A MINUTE.
THAT'S IT. LEMONADE.

08:11.115 --> 08:12.742
YEAH. I COULD
REALLY GO

08:12.825 --> 08:14.493
FOR A GLASS OF
LEMONADE RIGHT NOW.

08:14.577 --> 08:15.703
NO, CLOD.

08:15.786 --> 08:17.705
{\an1}SHE MEANS, WHEN LIFE
GIVES YOU LEMONS,

08:17.788 --> 08:19.415
MAKE LEMONADE.

08:19.498 --> 08:20.416
HUH?

08:19.498 --> 08:20.416
{\an1}YEAH.

08:20.499 --> 08:21.375
{\an7}WHEN THINGS GO BAD,
FIND A WAY

08:21.459 --> 08:23.961
{\an8}TO TURN IT INTO
SOMETHING GOOD,

08:24.045 --> 08:26.589
{\an7}AND THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M GOING TO DO.

08:26.672 --> 08:28.007
MY HEART IS BRIGHT!

08:28.090 --> 08:30.092
TIME TO BE A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

08:30.176 --> 08:31.928
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

08:32.010 --> 08:33.679
♪ IT'S TIME TO SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

08:33.763 --> 08:35.556
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

08:35.640 --> 08:37.558
♪ MY COURAGE SHINING BRIGHT ♪

08:37.642 --> 08:41.938
♪ NOW I AM
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

08:43.522 --> 08:44.732
NOW, THAT--

08:43.522 --> 08:44.732
"NOW, THAT'S

08:44.815 --> 08:47.068
A KNIGHT
IN SHINING ARMOR."

08:47.151 --> 08:48.819
{\an1}HEY, I WAS
GONNA SAY THAT.

08:48.903 --> 08:51.280
BLAINE: FRESHLY SCULPTED
BALLOON SWORDS.

08:51.364 --> 08:52.782
COME AND GET THEM.

08:52.865 --> 08:54.325
{\an1}I THINK I KNOW
HOW TO FIX THIS.

08:54.408 --> 08:56.786
{\an1}BLAINE, CAN I HAVE SOME
OF YOUR BALLOONS, PLEASE?

08:56.869 --> 08:59.622
WELL, WELL, WELL,
WHAT'S THE MATTER, NELLA,

08:59.705 --> 09:02.625
PEOPLE NOT SO INTO
YOUR FLOWERS ANYMORE?

09:02.708 --> 09:04.627
{\an1}BLAINE--

09:02.708 --> 09:04.627
YEP. THAT'S RIGHT.

09:04.710 --> 09:07.880
{\an1}EVERYONE DOWN THERE
IS COMING TO MY STAND NOW.

09:07.964 --> 09:11.300
"DOWN THERE"?

09:11.384 --> 09:13.302
OHH...NELLA, HELP!

09:13.386 --> 09:16.389
{\an1}COME ON, GUYS.
BLAINE NEEDS OUR HELP.

09:16.472 --> 09:18.683
GRAB AS MANY OF THOSE
BALLOONS AS YOU CAN.

09:18.766 --> 09:20.685
OK, BUT WHY?

09:20.768 --> 09:22.520
YOU'LL SEE.

09:22.603 --> 09:25.731
UP, UP, AND AWAY.

09:25.815 --> 09:26.732
MAN: GOOD LUCK.

09:26.816 --> 09:27.858
IDA: BE CAREFUL,
NELLA.

09:27.942 --> 09:29.360
UTA: GO, NELLA.

09:29.443 --> 09:30.653
OH, NOW I GET IT.

09:30.736 --> 09:32.989
IT'S LIKE
A HOT-AIR BALLOON.

09:33.072 --> 09:34.824
NELLA'S SO COOL.

09:34.907 --> 09:37.576
{\an8}"NO. SHE'S
THE COOLEST."

09:37.660 --> 09:40.162
{\an7}HOLD ON, BLAINE.
I'M COMING.

09:40.246 --> 09:42.581
{\an8}HURRY! WHOA!

09:42.665 --> 09:44.292
GOTCHA.

09:44.375 --> 09:46.002
NNGH!

09:44.375 --> 09:46.002
NNGH!

09:46.085 --> 09:48.587
OOH...WHOA!

09:46.085 --> 09:48.587
OH!

09:48.671 --> 09:50.631
AAH!

09:50.715 --> 09:52.842
NELLA, HELP!
WHOA!

09:52.925 --> 09:54.260
OK. TIME FOR PLAN "B."

09:54.343 --> 09:59.015
WHOA! HEY, BLAINE,
NEED A LIFT?

09:59.682 --> 10:00.725
NOW JUMP. HAH!

10:03.102 --> 10:04.812
WAY TO GO, NELLA.

10:03.102 --> 10:04.812
YEAH!

10:04.895 --> 10:07.064
OH, NELLA,
I'M SO SORRY.

10:07.148 --> 10:08.691
THIS IS
ALL MY FAULT.

10:08.774 --> 10:10.776
IT IS?

10:08.774 --> 10:10.776
YEAH.

10:10.860 --> 10:13.529
I WAS JEALOUS, SO I
RUINED YOUR FLOWERS.

10:13.612 --> 10:15.531
NOW IT LOOKS
LIKE I RUINED

10:15.615 --> 10:17.408
THE WHOLE SHARE
FAIRE, TOO.

10:17.491 --> 10:18.826
{\an1}AW, DON'T WORRY, BLAINE.
I HAVE A PLAN.

10:18.909 --> 10:22.580
{\an1}♪ WHEN THINGS LOOK BITTER,
MAKE IT ALL BETTER ♪

10:22.663 --> 10:24.373
{\an1}♪ IT'S ALL
GONNA BE OK ♪

10:24.457 --> 10:26.959
{\an1}BOTH: ♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

10:27.043 --> 10:29.378
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

10:29.462 --> 10:31.881
♪ WHEN THINGS GO WRONG,
JUST TURN THEM AROUND ♪

10:31.964 --> 10:34.300
♪ TURN LEMONS INTO LEMONADE ♪

10:34.383 --> 10:35.926
UTA: OOH,
THAT'S GOOD, NELLA.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.179
{\an1}GIRL: A FLOWERY
PLAYGROUND.

10:38.262 --> 10:40.264
WHOA!

10:42.058 --> 10:44.644
IT'S SO GOOD TO BE BACK
ON SOLID GROUND.

10:44.727 --> 10:45.686
{\an1}THANKS FOR
RESCUING ME, NELLA.

10:45.770 --> 10:50.232
{\an1}HERE. I WANT TO SHARE
SOMETHING WITH YOU.

10:51.108 --> 10:53.652
A BALLOON TIARA?
COOL.

10:53.736 --> 10:55.613
THANKS, BLAINE,
BUT YOU KNOW

10:55.696 --> 10:57.073
WHAT ELSE I'D LIKE?

10:57.156 --> 10:59.116
ONE OF YOUR GREAT
BALLOON SWORDS.

10:59.200 --> 11:00.785
YOU CAN'T BE
A PRINCESS KNIGHT

11:00.868 --> 11:02.953
WITHOUT A TIARA
AND A SWORD.

11:03.037 --> 11:05.122
